      "url": "",
      "abstract": "Generative AI에 관한 개념, 수식, 구현 내용을 정리한 학습 노트입니다.",
      "note": "## Generative Model\n\n### Generation\n\n- Data의 Probability Distribution이 Space 상에 존재\n- 해당 Probability Distribution에서 Point를 Sample하는 것\n- 만약 Probability Distribution를 알고 있다면, Directly Sampling 할 수 있음\n\n### Inverse Transform Sampling\n\n: PDF를 CDF로 변경 후 (0, 1)에서 Uniformly Sampling\n\n![image.png](./assets/study-notes/image%2019.png)\n\n1) Compute CDF $F(x)$\n\n2) Draw $u \\sim \\mathcal{U}(0, 1)$\n\n3) Take $x = F^{-1}(u)$   →   we have to know $F^{-1}$\n\n### Sampling from a Normal Distribution\n<Box-Muller Tranform>\n\n- PDF for Stand Normal Distribution $\\mathcal{N}(0, 1)$\n\n    : $p(x) = \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2\\pi}}exp(-\\frac{x^2}{2})$\n\n    ⇒ CDF를 Directly 계산 불\n\n- Box-Muller Transform\n    - Sampling $x,y \\sim \\mathcal{N}(0, 1)$ 를 한다고 생각\n\n        ⇒ $p(x, y) = p(x)p(y) = \\frac{1}{2\\pi}exp(-\\frac{x^2 + y^2}{2})$\n\n    - Tranform 2D Cartesian to Polar\n\n        : $x = r \\cos \\theta, \\; y = r \\sin \\theta, \\; d = x^2 + y^2$\n\n        ⇒ $p(\\theta, d) = p(\\theta)p(d) = p(x, d) \\cdot |detJ|$\n\n        ⇒ $\\theta \\sim \\mathcal{U} (0, 2\\pi)$ → $p({\\theta})=\\frac{1}{2\\pi}$\n\n        ⇒ $d \\sim \\mathcal{X}^2_2$ → $p(d)=\\frac{1}{2} exp(-\\frac{d}{2})$\n\n        ⇒ $p(\\theta, d) = \\frac{1}{2\\pi} \\cdot \\frac{1}{2} exp(-\\frac{d}{2})$\n\n    - Consider only $p(d)$\n\n        ⇒ PDF: $p(d)=\\frac{1}{2} exp(-\\frac{d}{2})$\n\n        ⇒ CDF: $F(d)= 1 - exp(-\\frac{d}{2})$\n\n        ⇒ $F^{-1}(u) = -2 \\ln{(1-u)}$\n\n    - Sampling\n        1. Draw $\\theta \\sim \\mathcal{U} (0, 2\\pi)$ and $u \\sim \\mathcal{U}(0, 1)$\n        2. Compute $d=-2\\ln(1-u)$ and $r=\\sqrt{d}$\n        3. Compute $x=r\\cos\\theta, \\; y=r\\sin\\theta$\n\n### Sampling from a Multivariate Normal\n\n- Multivariate Normal Distribution\n\n    ![image.png](./assets/study-notes/image%2020.png)\n\n    ⇒ $X$가 k-dimensional random vector\n\n    : $X = (X_1, ..., X_k)^T$\n\n    ⇒ $X \\sim \\mathcal{N}(\\mu, \\Sigma)$\n\n- Diagonal covariance Gaussian에서는 각 dimension을 independent하게 sampling\n- 일반 covariance Gaussian은 independent standard normal sample에 Cholesky factor 등을 곱해 상관관계를 반영\n\n### Sampling from a Anisotropic Normal\n\n- Isotropic Gaussian Distribution\n\n    ⇒ 차원간의 Correlation이 없는 Multivariate Normal\n\n    ⇒ Covariance가 대각 행렬이면서 모든 대각 성분이 동일\n\n- Anisotropic Gaussian Distribution\n\n    ⇒ 차원간의 Correlation이 있는 Multivariate Normal\n\n    ⇒ Covariance\n\n    ![image.png](./assets/study-notes/image%2021.png)\n\n- Sampling\n\n    : $z \\sim \\mathcal{Z}(\\mu, \\Sigma)$\n\n    ⇒ $z = \\mu + \\Sigma^{\\frac{1}{2}} \\cdot \\epsilon,\\;\\; \\epsilon \\sim \\mathcal{N}(0, I)$\n\n\n## Latent Representation for Generation\n\n- Data Distribution $p(x)$ 가 Too High-Dimensional Data\n(e.g., Image, Video, …)\n\n    ⇒ Sampling이 불가능\n\n- Mapping a **Simple Distribution $p(z)$** to the $p(x)$\n\n    ⇒ Sampling $z$ from simple $p(z)$ and map it to a data point\n\n    ![image.png](./assets/study-notes/image%2022.png)\n\n- **Get D(z) from Neural Network!**\n\n    ![image.png](./assets/study-notes/image%2023.png)\n\n    - Encoder: $E: z = p(x)$\n    - Decoder: $D: x = p(z)$\n    - 단순 Reconstruction만으로는 Latent가 Data Distribution의 Data Point인 x로 mapped되는지에 대한 **Gurantee를 갖지 못함**\n\n        ⇒ 이를 가능하게 만드는 것이 Generative Model\n\n\n---",
